message:
I need small clarification on [task.run](http://task.run) in the below piece of code:

List<object> items = GetItemsToProcess();  
int doneSoFar = 0;

foreach (var item in items)  
{  
 await Task.Run(() => SomeCpuIntensiveWorkAsync(item));

 doneSoFar++;

 int progressPercentage = (int)((double)doneSoFar / items.Count * 100);

 this.ProgressBar.Value = progressPercentage;  
}  
ProgressBar.value updates within the task block which executes on different thread. But I'm able to update the UI element without error. How is it possible when task is running on different thread?
